<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2847] Put added after a delete is overshadowed if its timestamp is older than than that of the tombstone</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2847</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we delete a row and then at a later time add to the row a cell that has a timestamp that is older than the delete, the addition will not be seen; the tombstone will prevent the newer addition being returned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;IMO, this is non-intuitive.  We should fix.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12469564">HBASE-2847</key>
            <summary>Put added after a delete is overshadowed if its timestamp is older than than that of the tombstone</summary>
