                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12889924" author="streamy" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2010 17:21:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is probably the hardest behavior to change because it requires looking at the type, not just the timestamp / memstore stamp / storefile order.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should fix multiple version issues first, for puts, and then consider this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12890002" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2010 20:21:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this will almost certainly require changing the data format and including more information with each KeyValue, probably another long (for sequence id or something).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12890010" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2010 20:35:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;another alternative is to disable setting timestamps - most of the&lt;br/&gt;
problems happen because people can set arbitrary timestamps, along&lt;br/&gt;
with deleting specific revisions. by removing those features we can&lt;br/&gt;
prevent the user from seeing the questionable behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12890086" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 19 Jul 2010 23:04:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;talking to stack it sounds like option #1 - adding in a new 8 byte long to the KeyValue would be the most likely choice at this point.  What exactly we will store in there is still up for grabs, it should ideally be something that helps implement ACID isolation along with this particular bug.  Choices include a region-specific per-edit counter, sequence_id or the actual timestamp.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918196" author="streamy" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 21:14:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Punting to 0.92.  This will not be done for 0.90, if ever.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13047631" author="stack" created="Fri, 10 Jun 2011 22:46:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving out of 0.92.0. Pull it back in if you think different.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14490628" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 11 Apr 2015 00:39:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Incomplete here. Rehashed several times in subsequent later issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
